  "title": "[PERM] Assistant Manager, Inpatient Ops",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>Clinical Service Development</p><ul><li>Oversee and manage all aspects of assigned clinical services.</li><li>Collaborate closely with multidisciplinary departments to ensure integrated, end-to-end service delivery and a positive patient experience across the continuum of care.</li><li>Plan and develop new clinical services as assigned, including:</li><li>Forecasting workload and service demand</li><li>Identifying and securing required resources and approvals</li><li>Managing project timelines to ensure on-time and within-budget delivery</li><li>Secure and manage budgets, monitor resource utilization, and oversee procurement of equipment and consumables to support clinic and/or ward operations.</li></ul><p>Clinical Initiative Support</p><ul><li>Support department-wide initiatives that impact clinical operations.</li><li>Coordinate with internal stakeholders (e.g. Legal, Communications) and external partners to facilitate initiative implementation and expansion.</li></ul><p>Other Ad-Hoc Duties</p><ul><li>Execute additional tasks and responsibilities as assigned by the Reporting Officer (RO) and Head of Department (HOD).</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in business, healthcare, or a related field.</li><li>Strong communication, interpersonal, planning, and organizational skills.</li><li>Ability to manage multiple priorities effectively in a fast-paced environment.</li><li>Team-oriented with the ability to work independently.</li><li>Positive, adaptable attitude with strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail.</li><li>Preferably 1 year of experience in project management, operations, or a related field (healthcare experience is an advantage but not required).</li><li>Familiarity with project management tools and strong proficiency in Microsoft Office.</li></ul><p>Please state your availability, current and expected salary in the resume.<br /></p><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified. </p><p>GMP Technologies (S) Pte Ltd   |   EA Licence: 11C3793   |   Eddie Tang |   Registration No: R1221129</p>",
